# Input Component for React Forms

The `Input` component is a flexible and reusable input field designed for React applications, integrating seamlessly with `react-hook-form` for efficient form handling and validation. It is styled with Tailwind CSS, providing a modern and responsive design.

## Features

- **React Hook Form Integration**: Easy form handling and validation with `react-hook-form`.
- **Customizable**: Supports labels, descriptions, custom validation messages, and all standard HTML input attributes.
- **Styled with Tailwind CSS**: Ensures a modern look and feel with responsive design.

## Propsx

label: string
Description: Text for the input field label.
Required: No

name: string
Description: Name attribute of the input for form submission.
Required: Yes

description: string
Description: Additional information about the input field.
Required: No

message: string
Description: Custom validation message for the input.
Required: No

register: UseFormRegister<any>
Description: Function from react-hook-form to register input.
Required: Yes

...props: InputHTMLAttributes
Description: Any other standard input attributes.
Required: No

## Installation and Usage

Ensure you have `react`, `react-hook-form`, and `tailwindcss` installed in your project before proceeding.
